  "decision_conditions": [
    "<p>The development, by reason of the complete loss of trees, natural features and soft landscaping, would result in the provision of insufficient sustainable drainage, failing to appropriately mitigate against potential flood risk.&nbsp; As such, the development is contrary to policies G7 (Trees and Woodlands), SI12 (Flood Risk Management) and SI 13 (Sustainable Drainage) of the London Plan 2021 and policies LP51 (Tree Management and Landscaping) and LP53 (Water and Flooding) of the Hackney Local Plan 2020.<br></p>",
    "&lt;p&gt;The development, by reason of the complete and unacceptable loss of trees, would result in the reduction of amenity and ecological values, contrary to good arboricultural practice. As such, the development is contrary to policy G7 (Trees and Woodlands) of the London Plan 2021 and policy LP51 (Tree Management and Landscaping) of the Hackney Local Plan 2020.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The development consisting of the change of the front boundary design and materials (including the replacement pillar) and the hardstanding of both front and rear gardens by reason of design and materials results in an incompatible form of development which fails to preserve or enhance the character and appearance of the building, the street scene, and the conservation area. As such, the development is contrary to policies D1 ‘London’s form, character and capacity for growth’, D3 ‘Optimising site capacity through the design-led approach’ and HC1 ‘Heritage conservation and growth’ of the London Plan 2021, policies LP1 ‘Design Quality and Local Character’ and LP3 ‘Designated Heritage Assets’ of the Hackney Local Plan 2020 and the development control principles contained within the Graham Road and Mapledene Conservation Area Appraisal 1997.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;"
  ],
